text: Rock the Vote is a nonpartisan non-profit organization in the United States. The main goal of the organization is to register young people to vote and to get them to vote in their local or national elections. The organization was founded in 1990 by Virgin Records America Co-Chairman Jeff Ayeroff. It is focused toward increasing voter turnout among voters ages 18 to 24. ==References== Category:Non-profit organizations of the United States
title: Rock the Vote
